36.04	Indian_religions	Indian religions	Indian religions is a classification for religions that originated in the Indian subcontinent; namely Hinduism, Jainism, Buddhism and Sikhism. These religions are also classified as Eastern religions. Although Indian religions are connected through the history of India, they constitute a wide range of religious communities and Indian religions are not confined to the Indian subcontinent.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Bangalore_Monument_.jpg/160px-Bangalore_Monument_.jpg
